1
00:00:02,310 --> 00:00:05,960
[Episode 11]
[Trading Life for an Eternal Bond]

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:04,570
No wonder everyone on the island knows

3
00:00:04,570 --> 00:00:06,170
you looked for Hong days ago.

4
00:00:07,100 --> 00:00:07,720
But why do you think

5
00:00:07,720 --> 00:00:09,490
he can undo the wish?

6
00:00:12,240 --> 00:00:13,610
My friend said

7
00:00:13,610 --> 00:00:15,940
Hong is not an ordinary person.

8
00:00:17,420 --> 00:00:18,560
Uncle Hua, did he

9
00:00:18,580 --> 00:00:20,550
talk to you before?

10
00:00:23,130 --> 00:00:23,770
No.

11
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:27,060
Even if he did say something,

12
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:28,690
I wouldn't care at all.

13
00:00:29,990 --> 00:00:31,560
You know what? For doctors,

14
00:00:32,159 --> 00:00:33,690
there are 2 kinds of people.

15
00:00:34,230 --> 00:00:35,630
One is the sick,

16
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:37,870
and the other is the healthy.

17
00:00:38,010 --> 00:00:39,540
So I don't think

18
00:00:39,570 --> 00:00:41,700
there's something special about him.

19
00:00:41,970 --> 00:00:43,070
True.

20
00:00:45,810 --> 00:00:46,710
But...

21
00:00:47,310 --> 00:00:48,040
Uncle Hua,

22
00:00:48,470 --> 00:00:49,710
after so many years,

23
00:00:50,010 --> 00:00:53,270
have you never thought
about returning to the main island?

24
00:00:54,570 --> 00:00:55,600
Once.

25
00:00:57,120 --> 00:00:59,550
As my guiding teacher lay dying,

26
00:01:00,460 --> 00:01:03,120
I got a boat ticket
and hurried back to visit him.

27
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:06,850
But suddenly there was a storm,

28
00:01:08,630 --> 00:01:10,830
causing all boat trips to be cancelled.

29
00:01:11,970 --> 00:01:13,970
Later, every time I bought a ticket,

30
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,670
some emergency would pop up,

31
00:01:18,410 --> 00:01:20,940
keeping me from going back
to the main island.

32
00:01:21,810 --> 00:01:22,980
So,

33
00:01:23,650 --> 00:01:26,110
this should be the consequence
of your wish.

34
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:28,940
Even if you want to go back,

35
00:01:29,410 --> 00:01:30,680
you just can't.

36
00:01:33,380 --> 00:01:34,410
That's fine.

37
00:01:37,930 --> 00:01:39,259
I've exiled myself

38
00:01:39,690 --> 00:01:40,960
to atone for my sins,

39
00:01:41,950 --> 00:01:44,420
so I can't choose to live a happy life.

40
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:48,970
I deserve this for being unable

41
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:53,390
to go back and meet my family and friends.

42
00:01:54,440 --> 00:01:55,840
But don't you think

43
00:01:55,960 --> 00:01:57,600
the price is too high?

44
00:01:58,180 --> 00:01:59,310
But for me,

45
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:02,310
a wish is a choice.

46
00:02:03,240 --> 00:02:05,070
Whether you get it or lose it

47
00:02:05,090 --> 00:02:07,030
depends on your perspective.

48
00:02:08,889 --> 00:02:09,919
As for...

49
00:02:11,230 --> 00:02:13,130
whether my wish gets undone,

50
00:02:14,660 --> 00:02:16,160
I don't really care.

51
00:02:18,030 --> 00:02:19,070
I accept it,

52
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:20,960
and I'm willing to face it.

53
00:02:28,210 --> 00:02:30,540
So I'll continue to fight against my wish.

54
00:02:31,950 --> 00:02:33,540
I don't want to give up on myself.

55
00:02:33,540 --> 00:02:35,340
I want to find He Xiangyong back.

56
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:37,930
This is the way I face it.

57
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:47,000
Thank you, Uncle Hua.

58
00:02:53,970 --> 00:02:54,670
Uncle Hua.

59
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:58,850
You speak so lightly,

60
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:00,940
yet I can tell

61
00:03:00,940 --> 00:03:02,340
you haven't truly let go.

62
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:04,600
Actually, you don't need to.

63
00:03:06,090 --> 00:03:07,090
Just make peace

64
00:03:07,110 --> 00:03:08,240
and embrace it.

65
00:03:11,050 --> 00:03:12,290
Bravely accept

66
00:03:12,290 --> 00:03:13,860
your once broken self,

67
00:03:14,890 --> 00:03:16,820
and you can become a better person.

68
00:03:17,460 --> 00:03:18,700
I sincerely hope

69
00:03:18,730 --> 00:03:21,860
you can go back to the main island
and save lives someday.

70
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:25,470
I can also save lives here.

71
00:03:28,410 --> 00:03:30,280
I also hope you can save yourself.

72
00:03:32,230 --> 00:03:33,700
Save your old self

73
00:03:33,980 --> 00:03:35,180
trapped in that time.

74
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:33,950
[Wishing Upon the Shooting Stars]

75
00:04:36,300 --> 00:04:38,409
Mom, I'm home!

76
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,640
You finally know to come home?

77
00:04:40,640 --> 00:04:42,680
I thought you were from the main island.

78
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:43,980
Don't say that.

79
00:04:43,980 --> 00:04:45,510
I brought you a surprise.

80
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,250
I brought you

81
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:49,780
what you keep talking about every morning—

82
00:04:49,780 --> 00:04:51,950
Chocola BB Plus from Japan.

83
00:04:52,790 --> 00:04:54,600
You want an advance on your salary?

84
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,700
No.

85
00:04:56,180 --> 00:04:57,800
Don't you talk about it every morning?

86
00:04:57,800 --> 00:05:00,060
Top up your B vitamins to stay energized.

87
00:05:01,380 --> 00:05:02,650
It's rare

88
00:05:02,930 --> 00:05:05,330
to see you restock my supplies
on your own.

89
00:05:05,420 --> 00:05:06,580
Of course.

90
00:05:06,650 --> 00:05:08,480
After all, people prefer gifting health

91
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,510
over flowers these days.

92
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:10,580
Don't you say

93
00:05:10,610 --> 00:05:11,360
eating this

94
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:12,840
helps with nutrition and overall health

95
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,240
and makes you look good

96
00:05:14,270 --> 00:05:15,840
and always beautiful?

97
00:05:16,340 --> 00:05:18,050
You're so sweet.

98
00:05:19,810 --> 00:05:22,220
Did you hit the jackpot prize?

99
00:05:24,450 --> 00:05:25,320
Bingo.

100
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:26,640
I won the lottery.

101
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:28,920
Let me tell you.

102
00:05:28,920 --> 00:05:30,690
I checked out a plot of land
a couple of days ago,

103
00:05:30,690 --> 00:05:31,660
and I think its location is—

104
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:33,130
It's not like that.

105
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:35,030
I hit the jackpot in love.

106
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,560
Couldn't you have said that sooner?

107
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,170
Yesterday,

108
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:43,290
I confessed to Hama-chan.

109
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,170
You're fond of Hama-chan?

110
00:05:51,110 --> 00:05:52,409
That sounds familiar.

111
00:05:52,670 --> 00:05:53,870
When did I say that?

112
00:05:56,080 --> 00:05:57,290
Why didn't I know?

113
00:05:58,350 --> 00:06:00,590
There are many things you don't know.

114
00:06:01,840 --> 00:06:02,700
Tell me.

115
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,720
Is there anything else I don't know?

116
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:06,230
Nothing.

117
00:06:06,450 --> 00:06:07,850
Just remember one thing.

118
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:09,370
Hama-chan made the first move.

119
00:06:09,370 --> 00:06:10,390
Hama-chan likes me.

120
00:06:10,390 --> 00:06:12,050
That's why I confessed to him.

121
00:06:23,660 --> 00:06:24,730
So,

122
00:06:24,750 --> 00:06:27,680
are you going to have
a long-distance relationship?

123
00:06:28,850 --> 00:06:29,680
Let me tell you,

124
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,890
this is a big test.

125
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:32,220
Be mentally prepared.

126
00:06:33,330 --> 00:06:34,470
What long distance?

127
00:06:34,490 --> 00:06:36,290
The dock is so close to our house.

128
00:06:36,659 --> 00:06:39,060
No, Zhong came
to eat shaved ice yesterday.

129
00:06:39,409 --> 00:06:42,450
He said Hama-chan
wants to sail around the world.

130
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:46,180
He's going to sign a contract
with a deep-sea fleet.

131
00:06:55,890 --> 00:06:57,650
If he hasn't told you,

132
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:59,409
he might not have made up his mind,

133
00:06:59,409 --> 00:07:00,050
right?

134
00:07:00,050 --> 00:07:01,820
It's fine, really.

135
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,170
It's okay.

136
00:07:04,910 --> 00:07:05,910
Thank you.

137
00:07:05,930 --> 00:07:07,600
-Thank you.
-It's okay.

138
00:07:24,650 --> 00:07:27,220
I've got a Japanese crew member lately.

139
00:07:28,630 --> 00:07:29,950
You can speak Japanese.

140
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:31,650
Can you help me talk to him?

141
00:07:31,710 --> 00:07:32,810
We need to fit in more.

142
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:34,180
I'll buy you sashimi then.

143
00:07:34,180 --> 00:07:34,880
Great!

144
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,530
Are you from Japan?

145
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:43,020
Don't mess with me.

146
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,370
Well, excuse me,

147
00:07:44,470 --> 00:07:45,510
I'm a newbie.

148
00:07:51,520 --> 00:07:53,120
Use this. Be careful.

149
00:07:56,770 --> 00:07:58,500
Don't lump everyone together.

150
00:07:58,820 --> 00:08:01,150
Not all Japanese people love ramen,

151
00:08:01,170 --> 00:08:03,030
read comics, or play video games.

152
00:08:03,610 --> 00:08:05,020
Lump everyone together.

153
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,240
You can speak idioms?

154
00:08:07,950 --> 00:08:09,120
I must tell my mom about this.

155
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:09,750
Come on.

156
00:08:10,540 --> 00:08:11,390
Stop recording.

157
00:08:11,390 --> 00:08:12,590
Come on. Say another one.

158
00:08:12,590 --> 00:08:13,490
The last one.

159
00:08:14,740 --> 00:08:16,540
A black jar holds soy sauce—

160
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:18,220
you can't tell what's inside.

161
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:20,310
You're amazing!

162
00:08:34,020 --> 00:08:34,860
Li Wanzhe,

163
00:08:35,190 --> 00:08:36,250
what are you doing?

164
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:44,320
You said you had something to tell me.

165
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:46,580
So you just want me
to drink with you, huh?

166
00:08:46,950 --> 00:08:47,820
Cheers.

167
00:08:48,730 --> 00:08:49,630
No.

168
00:08:50,340 --> 00:08:51,870
Stop drinking.

169
00:08:55,160 --> 00:08:56,220
What are you doing?

170
00:08:59,430 --> 00:09:00,500
What do you mean?

171
00:09:05,390 --> 00:09:06,310
What's wrong with you?

172
00:09:06,310 --> 00:09:07,520
Calm down.

173
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:08,450
Shut up.

174
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:15,170
Let me go!

175
00:09:16,220 --> 00:09:17,420
Are you drunk?

176
00:09:18,020 --> 00:09:19,190
Yes, I'm drunk.

177
00:09:31,650 --> 00:09:32,750
Li Wanzhe.

178
00:09:33,900 --> 00:09:35,240
Are you serious?

179
00:09:37,090 --> 00:09:38,750
I've never been this serious.

180
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:34,370
In your view,

181
00:12:34,940 --> 00:12:36,070
what is love?

182
00:12:38,870 --> 00:12:40,740
Love is short-lived eternity.

183
00:12:41,320 --> 00:12:42,320
Being happy together each day

184
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:43,450
is all that matters.

185
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:46,820
What about me?

186
00:12:49,330 --> 00:12:51,100
I like you very, very,

187
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,330
very much.

188
00:12:53,070 --> 00:12:54,440
No matter where I am,

189
00:12:55,070 --> 00:12:56,530
you're always in my heart.

190
00:13:01,540 --> 00:13:03,870
If anyone tries
to hit on you abroad later,

191
00:13:04,050 --> 00:13:04,950
make sure you tell them

192
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:05,750
you already belong to someone,

193
00:13:05,750 --> 00:13:06,490
got it?

194
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:18,730
I want to date!

195
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:20,030
Like fireworks!

196
00:13:20,050 --> 00:13:21,120
Whoosh!

197
00:13:21,150 --> 00:13:21,980
Bang!

198
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:24,120
Could it be...

199
00:13:24,360 --> 00:13:25,760
that all of this came true

200
00:13:26,010 --> 00:13:28,020
because of a wish?

201
00:13:30,880 --> 00:13:31,610
I'm tired.

202
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,130
I can give you a massage.

203
00:13:36,300 --> 00:13:37,270
It's okay.

204
00:13:38,220 --> 00:13:39,750
Let's get some sleep, okay?

205
00:13:53,010 --> 00:13:54,710
Where am I?

206
00:13:58,360 --> 00:13:59,160
Dad.

207
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:01,320
Dad.

208
00:14:03,300 --> 00:14:04,070
Dad.

209
00:14:15,300 --> 00:14:16,240
Li Wanzhe.

210
00:14:17,130 --> 00:14:18,000
Li Wanzhe.

211
00:14:20,910 --> 00:14:22,080
He Xiangyong.

212
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:24,310
Chen Haowei.

213
00:14:26,850 --> 00:14:27,820
Chen Haowei.

214
00:14:31,420 --> 00:14:32,820
Don't waste your energy.

215
00:14:35,620 --> 00:14:36,490
Hong,

216
00:14:36,490 --> 00:14:37,760
you've finally shown up.

217
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:38,760
Can you help me?

218
00:14:40,290 --> 00:14:42,100
Why do you think I can help you?

219
00:14:42,460 --> 00:14:44,720
Since you chose to abandon He Xiangyong,

220
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,470
he won't come back then.

221
00:14:46,470 --> 00:14:48,670
This is something I can't change.

222
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:50,500
It's your wish,

223
00:14:50,740 --> 00:14:51,970
your choice.

224
00:14:52,370 --> 00:14:53,770
Even if you regret it now,

225
00:14:54,010 --> 00:14:55,440
you have to accept it.

226
00:14:57,210 --> 00:14:58,310
No.

227
00:14:58,580 --> 00:14:59,250
Well,

228
00:14:59,250 --> 00:15:00,750
can I cancel my wish?

229
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:02,080
I'm not Zhong Xiaoyou anymore.

230
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:04,010
Give He Xiangyong back to me, okay?

231
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,820
Humans.

232
00:15:06,520 --> 00:15:08,420
The true value of a wish

233
00:15:08,690 --> 00:15:10,220
lies not in gaining what you want,

234
00:15:10,220 --> 00:15:11,590
but in how you face it.

235
00:15:12,060 --> 00:15:13,330
Even if the outcome...

236
00:15:13,330 --> 00:15:13,730
Dad!

237
00:15:13,730 --> 00:15:15,000
is what we call loss...

238
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:15,930
Chen Haowei!

239
00:15:15,930 --> 00:15:17,360
you have to experience it.

240
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:18,630
Chen Haowei!

241
00:15:18,630 --> 00:15:19,530
Otherwise,

242
00:15:19,530 --> 00:15:20,470
it'd be such a waste.

243
00:15:20,470 --> 00:15:21,170
I beg you.

244
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:22,100
I was wrong!

245
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:22,940
I was wrong!

246
00:15:22,940 --> 00:15:24,140
Can I cancel my wish?

247
00:15:24,140 --> 00:15:25,170
I don't want to be Zhong Xiaoyou anymore.

248
00:15:25,170 --> 00:15:26,540
Give He Xiangyong back to me.

249
00:15:26,540 --> 00:15:27,540
Dad!

250
00:15:27,540 --> 00:15:28,540
I'm He Xiangyong!

251
00:15:28,540 --> 00:15:30,010
I'm He Xiangyong!

252
00:15:30,010 --> 00:15:30,710
Xiangyong.

253
00:15:30,710 --> 00:15:31,580
Xiangyong.

254
00:15:32,010 --> 00:15:33,050
Are you kidding me?

255
00:15:33,050 --> 00:15:34,580
How can I not recognize my own son?

256
00:15:34,580 --> 00:15:35,480
Xiangyong!

257
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:36,320
It's Xiangyong!

258
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:37,480
Xiangyong, what brings you back?

259
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:38,120
He Xiangyong.

260
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:38,790
He Xiangyong!

261
00:15:38,790 --> 00:15:39,650
You don't know him, either?

262
00:15:39,650 --> 00:15:40,590
No.

263
00:15:40,590 --> 00:15:42,060
The person I can't let go of
is He Xiangyong.

264
00:15:42,060 --> 00:15:43,020
He Xiangyong?

265
00:15:43,460 --> 00:15:44,430
Who?

266
00:15:44,430 --> 00:15:46,210
The person I've always loved
is also He Xiangyong.

267
00:15:46,210 --> 00:15:47,110
He Xiangyong,

268
00:15:47,130 --> 00:15:48,500
if he's like you,

269
00:15:48,530 --> 00:15:50,390
I'll kick the hell out of him!

270
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:51,600
I'm He Xiangyong!

271
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:52,930
I'm He Xiangyong!

272
00:15:52,930 --> 00:15:54,440
Please don't leave, okay?

273
00:15:55,640 --> 00:15:56,540
No!

274
00:15:57,810 --> 00:15:58,440
No.

275
00:15:58,670 --> 00:15:59,870
I'm He Xiangyong.

276
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:01,130
I'm He Xiangyong.

277
00:16:01,980 --> 00:16:02,680
Chen Haowei,

278
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:03,310
I'm He Xiangyong.

279
00:16:03,310 --> 00:16:03,910
Trust me.

280
00:16:03,910 --> 00:16:04,810
I'm He Xiangyong.

281
00:16:04,810 --> 00:16:05,880
Don't leave me, okay?

282
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:06,710
-Okay.
-I'm He Xiangyong.

283
00:16:06,710 --> 00:16:07,850
-I trust you.
-Trust me.

284
00:16:07,850 --> 00:16:08,380
-Trust me.
-Okay.

285
00:16:08,380 --> 00:16:09,520
-I'm really He Xiangyong.
-I trust you.

286
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,180
-I trust—
-Really.

287
00:16:10,180 --> 00:16:11,190
I trust you.

288
00:16:12,220 --> 00:16:13,350
You had a nightmare?

289
00:16:13,750 --> 00:16:15,120
I dreamed of Hong.

290
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,720
He wanted me to accept the loss of my wish

291
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,830
and accept the fact
that He Xiangyong will never exist again.

292
00:16:18,830 --> 00:16:19,630
No.

293
00:16:19,630 --> 00:16:20,490
I'm He Xiangyong.

294
00:16:20,490 --> 00:16:21,030
I'm He Xiangyong.

295
00:16:21,030 --> 00:16:21,630
-Trust me.
-Alright.

296
00:16:21,630 --> 00:16:22,360
Alright.

297
00:16:23,730 --> 00:16:25,260
It's a dream. It's not true.

298
00:16:26,670 --> 00:16:27,400
No.

299
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,940
This dream is real.

300
00:16:29,500 --> 00:16:30,870
And it's different now.

301
00:16:31,170 --> 00:16:32,570
If your dream represents
what happened in the past,

302
00:16:32,570 --> 00:16:33,700
what about my dream?

303
00:16:33,940 --> 00:16:35,640
It must be something
that will happen in the future.

304
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:36,440
No way.

305
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:37,850
I don't want He Xiangyong to disappear.

306
00:16:37,850 --> 00:16:38,610
What if Hong...

307
00:16:38,610 --> 00:16:40,310
What should I do if Hong doesn't help me?

308
00:16:40,310 --> 00:16:41,150
Alright.

309
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:48,460
No matter what happens to you,

310
00:16:49,690 --> 00:16:51,390
I'll always be by your side.

311
00:16:54,960 --> 00:16:56,900
Just as you promised to catch me,

312
00:16:58,730 --> 00:17:00,230
I'll catch you.

313
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:05,069
I don't want to disappear.

314
00:17:06,810 --> 00:17:08,540
I don't want to disappear.

315
00:17:11,349 --> 00:17:13,109
It's okay now.

316
00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:25,030
Angela.

317
00:17:25,030 --> 00:17:25,660
Let me tell you.

318
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:26,560
-We're here.
-When we were young...

319
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:29,260
Turning our island into your resort

320
00:17:29,260 --> 00:17:30,800
is an excellent choice.

321
00:17:30,950 --> 00:17:33,270
And the elders here have an old legend.

322
00:17:33,300 --> 00:17:35,770
As long as you throw rocks into the sea

323
00:17:35,770 --> 00:17:37,340
to exchange energy with shooting stars,

324
00:17:37,340 --> 00:17:38,910
your wish will come true.

325
00:17:39,010 --> 00:17:40,570
This will be a big selling point

326
00:17:40,570 --> 00:17:41,340
for the group's resort project.

327
00:17:41,340 --> 00:17:42,680
-Li Wanzhe, come and help!
-Right?

328
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:45,490
When the shooting stars come,

329
00:17:45,620 --> 00:17:47,870
throw their fragments into the sea!

330
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:48,970
Pop!

331
00:17:50,220 --> 00:17:51,020
Got it?

332
00:17:51,450 --> 00:17:53,050
When your wish merges

333
00:17:53,420 --> 00:17:54,690
with this energy,

334
00:17:55,590 --> 00:17:56,590
it will come true.

335
00:17:56,590 --> 00:17:58,260
We have to put it in the fridge.

336
00:17:58,260 --> 00:17:59,360
Where should I put it?

337
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:00,060
Just take it out.

338
00:18:00,060 --> 00:18:00,760
Rocks.

339
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:01,360
Li Wanzhe.

340
00:18:01,360 --> 00:18:01,900
Take it here.

341
00:18:01,900 --> 00:18:02,830
Come here.

342
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,300
What are you doing?

343
00:18:04,300 --> 00:18:05,300
Give me 5 minutes.

344
00:18:05,900 --> 00:18:06,630
Okay.

345
00:18:10,540 --> 00:18:11,770
Talk. Five minutes.

346
00:18:12,210 --> 00:18:13,510
The rock from the cave.

347
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:15,480
Someone must have thrown
the rock into the sea

348
00:18:15,480 --> 00:18:16,840
when we were making wishes.

349
00:18:16,840 --> 00:18:18,880
That's why our wishes have come true.

350
00:18:18,880 --> 00:18:19,750
So?

351
00:18:20,280 --> 00:18:21,120
So...

352
00:18:21,380 --> 00:18:23,350
so if we pick up the rock,

353
00:18:23,620 --> 00:18:25,550
our wish might be canceled, right?

354
00:18:25,850 --> 00:18:27,090
Crazy.

355
00:18:27,340 --> 00:18:28,510
The sea is so big.

356
00:18:28,540 --> 00:18:29,940
How can you pick it up?

357
00:18:31,890 --> 00:18:32,860
What do you mean?

358
00:18:33,830 --> 00:18:36,030
You don't want to solve the problem now?

359
00:18:36,500 --> 00:18:37,460
I'm fine now.

360
00:18:37,460 --> 00:18:38,500
I'm totally fine.

361
00:18:38,500 --> 00:18:39,970
But I'm not!

362
00:18:40,630 --> 00:18:41,300
I...

363
00:18:41,540 --> 00:18:42,570
No one knows

364
00:18:42,570 --> 00:18:43,670
who He Xiangyong is!

365
00:18:43,670 --> 00:18:44,410
If this continues,

366
00:18:44,410 --> 00:18:46,340
I might disappear from this world!

367
00:18:46,710 --> 00:18:48,110
It's none of my business.

368
00:18:51,670 --> 00:18:52,500
Yes.

369
00:18:53,250 --> 00:18:54,080
The disappearance of me

370
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:55,380
doesn't matter to you.

371
00:18:56,220 --> 00:18:57,280
What about Soukai?

372
00:18:58,820 --> 00:19:00,690
You and Soukai are just good now.

373
00:19:01,060 --> 00:19:02,020
Once your wish starts to backfire,

374
00:19:02,020 --> 00:19:03,680
it'll be too late for regrets.

375
00:19:05,220 --> 00:19:06,680
Are you trying to scare me?

376
00:19:09,260 --> 00:19:10,200
Are you scared?

377
00:19:12,560 --> 00:19:14,420
You're actually worried, right?

378
00:19:17,570 --> 00:19:18,510
Li Wanzhe,

379
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:20,040
I know you too well.

380
00:19:21,140 --> 00:19:23,800
We're close as brothers
who grew up side by side.

381
00:19:25,010 --> 00:19:27,110
You've always been a coward.

382
00:19:28,110 --> 00:19:30,440
You only run away when something happens.

383
00:19:31,350 --> 00:19:32,690
So you're scared now.

384
00:19:33,820 --> 00:19:35,980
You're afraid that if I really
pick up the rock,

385
00:19:35,980 --> 00:19:37,640
Soukai won't love you, right?

386
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:43,300
I've told you about Soukai.

387
00:19:43,830 --> 00:19:45,230
If you keep running away,

388
00:19:46,030 --> 00:19:47,630
your wish will fade away

389
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:49,700
just like fireworks,

390
00:19:49,950 --> 00:19:51,280
gone once they burn out.

391
00:19:52,340 --> 00:19:53,270
That's it.

392
00:19:56,710 --> 00:19:58,110
You call me your brother.

393
00:19:58,810 --> 00:20:02,010
Would a brother be this selfish
to someone he cares about?

394
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,550
I won't allow you

395
00:20:03,550 --> 00:20:05,730
to ruin my relationship
with Soukai in any way.

396
00:20:05,730 --> 00:20:07,060
You keep saying

397
00:20:07,120 --> 00:20:08,190
you'll disappear.

398
00:20:08,620 --> 00:20:09,290
Have you ever thought

399
00:20:09,290 --> 00:20:10,360
that maybe you don't deserve

400
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:11,560
to live in this world?

401
00:20:11,690 --> 00:20:13,220
What are you talking about?

402
00:20:13,660 --> 00:20:14,260
I'm sorry.

403
00:20:19,530 --> 00:20:20,460
Li Wanzhe,

404
00:20:20,530 --> 00:20:21,600
are you crazy?

405
00:20:26,940 --> 00:20:28,040
Li Wanzhe!

406
00:20:30,810 --> 00:20:32,210
What exactly do you want?

407
00:20:33,110 --> 00:20:34,110
Tell me!

408
00:20:34,380 --> 00:20:35,380
What's going on?

409
00:20:35,980 --> 00:20:36,680
Get up and fight!

410
00:20:36,680 --> 00:20:37,320
Stop fighting!

411
00:20:37,320 --> 00:20:39,420
What's going on? Why are you fighting?

412
00:20:39,420 --> 00:20:40,420
Stop fighting!

413
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:41,190
Come on!

414
00:20:41,190 --> 00:20:42,090
Weren't you moving things?

415
00:20:42,090 --> 00:20:43,090
-Don't you want to fight?
-Why are you fighting?

416
00:20:43,090 --> 00:20:44,020
Come here!

417
00:20:44,290 --> 00:20:45,490
Stop it!

418
00:20:45,860 --> 00:20:46,990
Stop it!

419
00:20:47,020 --> 00:20:47,990
You guys!

420
00:20:49,300 --> 00:20:50,430
All right!

421
00:20:51,370 --> 00:20:52,230
Stop fighting!

422
00:20:52,240 --> 00:20:53,470
Calm down!

423
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:56,170
Why did you fight?

424
00:20:56,940 --> 00:20:58,200
Why did you hit Wanzhe?

425
00:20:58,810 --> 00:20:59,580
So annoying.

426
00:21:04,420 --> 00:21:05,830
Everything's broken!

427
00:21:34,810 --> 00:21:35,710
Are you okay?

428
00:21:44,150 --> 00:21:45,680
Luckily, Mr. He is not here.

429
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:48,020
If he knew you fought,

430
00:21:48,890 --> 00:21:50,090
he would scold you.

431
00:21:52,730 --> 00:21:54,290
Just let him.

432
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:56,600
Just curse me to death.

433
00:21:58,600 --> 00:22:00,230
What was I doing?

434
00:22:00,570 --> 00:22:02,240
Why was I so impulsive?

435
00:22:05,710 --> 00:22:07,540
You were too impulsive just now.

436
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:11,310
The one who started it was wrong anyway.

437
00:22:12,580 --> 00:22:14,310
That's not the problem.

438
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:16,350
He is Li Wanzhe.

439
00:22:16,990 --> 00:22:18,320
We've known each other for over 20 years.

440
00:22:18,320 --> 00:22:19,920
We fought for the first time.

441
00:22:19,950 --> 00:22:21,480
I was the one who started it.

442
00:22:23,330 --> 00:22:24,810
He won't forgive me.

443
00:22:35,630 --> 00:22:38,760
Actually, I don't agree with you
about finding the rock.

444
00:22:43,610 --> 00:22:44,540
The sea is so big,

445
00:22:44,950 --> 00:22:46,280
yet the rock is so small.

446
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:47,410
How can you find it?

447
00:22:49,210 --> 00:22:51,510
Looking for the rock is my only hope now.

448
00:22:51,980 --> 00:22:53,240
I haven't even looked for it.

449
00:22:53,240 --> 00:22:54,810
Why are you denying it too?

450
00:22:56,060 --> 00:22:56,850
No.

451
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:03,100
I just hope you can be fine.

452
00:23:05,530 --> 00:23:07,830
I have to find He Xiangyong to get better.

453
00:23:14,710 --> 00:23:15,450
Forget it.

454
00:23:16,540 --> 00:23:18,140
You won't understand it now.

455
00:23:54,820 --> 00:23:57,250
Looking for the rock is my only hope now.

456
00:23:57,250 --> 00:23:59,620
I have to find He Xiangyong to get better.

457
00:24:36,820 --> 00:24:37,990
Let me

458
00:24:38,890 --> 00:24:40,660
find He Xiangyong for you.

459
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:10,880
[Epilogue]

460
00:27:43,310 --> 00:27:45,410
Why bother exposing it?

461
00:27:46,610 --> 00:27:49,320
Making a wish is a trial of choice.

462
00:27:50,330 --> 00:27:51,670
Every choice,

463
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:53,230
every beginning and end,

464
00:27:53,940 --> 00:27:55,540
has its own meaning

465
00:27:56,290 --> 00:27:58,460
and values that must exist.

466
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:04,960
I don't want to stand by and watch.

467
00:28:06,990 --> 00:28:08,620
This is not your story.

468
00:28:10,300 --> 00:28:12,140
We are both bystanders.

469
00:28:13,340 --> 00:28:14,840
We have no right to interfere

470
00:28:14,840 --> 00:28:16,680
and alter these choices.

471
00:29:09,130 --> 00:29:11,360
You have to bear all the consequences
of your wish, good or bad.

472
00:29:09,300 --> 00:29:14,900
[Next Episode]

473
00:29:11,630 --> 00:29:13,470
This is the path you must walk

474
00:29:13,930 --> 00:29:15,340
once your wish comes true.

475
00:29:15,340 --> 00:29:16,240
Your subconscious

476
00:29:16,240 --> 00:29:17,970
has led your life to this point.

477
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:20,070
Now you're just blaming it on fate.

478
00:29:20,070 --> 00:29:21,840
Who started all this?

479
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:23,280
And who was it that grew unsatisfied
with the wish

480
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:25,450
and foolishly tried to change it?
